column1: Which NFL team will win Super Bowl LIII?

column6: Rams phoned it in from the start.
4th quarter interception, less than 5 minutes remaining

As an Angeleno, I am making this prediction mostly on gut and desire, not logic. But also: “L.A. finished near the top of the league in virtually every meaningful stat on offense this season.” according to CBS Sports
Everyone is sick of the New England Patriots winning everything all the time. Unfortunately they will probably win again.

Rams have had 4 Super Bowl appearances, yet no wins - meanwhile the Patriots have had the most appearances (11) with 5 championship wins. 538 puts the odds at 53% for the Patriots and 47% for the Rams, however 538 indicates that they are 'conservative' with their odds. Knowing next to nothing about football, I would put my bets on the Patriots picking up their 6th championship win.
I hate myself for this but the Patriots do win a lot.

Patriots have a strong running game, and a quarterback/coach duo with a lot of experience. The Rams don't have a good record against the run and they don't have a lot of experience at their quarterback or coach position.

Experience in the playoffs is super important. Tom Brady and Bill Belichick have been here together now 9 times. Coming off a huge road win in Kansas city. The patriots are fired up. The patriot defense held Patrick Mahomes to 0 points in the first half. If the patriots can get the Rams defense tired quickly, they should have no problem getting their 6th Lombardi trophy.

I don't think the Patriots will be able to match the firepower of the Rams offense. It is unlikely they will be able to pressure Goff like the Bears were able to during the season. Pressure on Goff is what can slow down/stall that offense.
Not sure why this question was reissued...
